    "narrative": "For this slate, the model identifies **Matt Chapman** (70.06), **Luis Arraez** (69.53), and **Jung Hoo Lee** (68.02) as our cornerstones, largely fueled by a highly favorable matchup against Walker Buehler. The soft expected ERA (4.91) for Buehler combined with favorable wind conditions provides a meaningful boost for this contingent. **Bryson Stott** (72.63) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (72.31) actually edge out the top trio in total efficiency, with **Bryson Stott** benefiting significantly from a +14% SP skill adjustment against Luis Severino and a high dynamic platoon advantage. Meanwhile, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a must-start despite the tough matchup; even with a slight penalty for the catcher-focused defensive alignment, his base projection and order placement continue to anchor our output.\n\nPlatoon advantages are driving several of our decisions, most notably for **Gleyber Torres** (67.46) and **Wenceel Perez** (64.22), both of whom capitalize on a strong L-handed matchup against Jovani Mor\u00e1n. **Tyler Freeman** (63.65) is another high-value play today; despite a moderate matchup, a significant park factor boost of +14% and a high probability of stolen base opportunities against a slow-delivering pitcher make him an essential asset in our quest to dominate the SB category. The most difficult bench decision involved **Jeremiah Jackson**, who hovered near the 53-point mark. While he remains a capable utility option, he was squeezed out by the sheer volume of high-scoring platoon-advantaged bats. The risk for today remains the \"Lineup Pending\" status for almost every player; should **Cal Raleigh** or **Will Smith** move down in the order, their efficiency scores will likely regress, necessitating a potential shift in our approach to maintain our cap management strategy.",
